    • subWordToInt

      int subWordToInt(int begin, int end)
      Returns a range of bits as an int. (e.g. Word(0b1110_1111).subWordToInt(4, 5) should return 0).
      Parameters:
      begin - the first bit (inclusive), and must be >= 0 and invalid input: '<'= 7
      end - the last bit (exclusive), and must be >= 1 and invalid input: '<'= 8
      Returns:
      the selected bits as an int

      int subWordToIntSignExtend(int begin, int end)
      Returns a range of bits, sign-extended back to a 16-bit size, as an int.
      Parameters:
      begin - the first bit (inclusive), and must be >= 0 and invalid input: '<'= 7
      end - the last bit (exclusive), and must be >= 1 and invalid input: '<'= 8
      Returns:
      the selected bits as an intd `end` behave the same as in `subWordToInt(int begin, int end)`.
